        "summary":  "Google announced the general availability of the Interactions API, its unified endpoint for Gemini models and agents, moving out of public beta that launched in December 2025. The API supports server-side state management, background execution, combined tool use, and multimodal generation in a single interface. It introduces Managed Agents for autonomous task execution and replaces the legacy generateContent API as the recommended development path.",
        "execSummary":  "Google has standardized its AI platform around a single API surface that handles both models and agents with persistent state ΓÇö a significant architectural shift from per-request stateless calls. For enterprise platform and engineering leaders, this means new integrations should be built against the Interactions API now to avoid a migration later, as the legacy generateContent API is being phased to secondary status. The background execution and tool combination capabilities are purpose-built for enterprise automation workflows. Teams building on Google Cloud should validate existing integrations against the new endpoint before it becomes the enforced default.",
        "vendorLean":  "Google ΓÇö promotes Google Cloud and Gemini developer platform.",
