        "execSummary":  "DXC\u0027s report that Claude wrote over 95% of code for a production platform is among the strongest real-world evidence yet of AI-native development at scale in an enterprise IT services context. For senior leaders, the four focus areas ΓÇö legacy modernization, cybersecurity ops, insurance automation, and application management ΓÇö map directly to the highest-cost, highest-risk line items in enterprise IT budgets. The multi-year commitment with certified engineer training indicates DXC is treating Claude as a platform dependency, not a pilot tool, which de-risks adoption for DXC\u0027s own client base. Organizations currently engaged with DXC as a systems integrator should ask explicitly how Claude capabilities are being incorporated into their existing contracts and roadmaps.",
