        "summary":  "Anthropic published details on the cybersecurity safeguards built into Claude Fable 5 and introduced a proposed Cyber Jailbreak Severity (CJS) scale rated 0-4 across four dimensions: capability gain, breadth of capability gain, ease of weaponization, and discoverability. The framework classifies model safety behaviors into four tiers ranging from prohibited use to benign use, and Anthropic is positioning the CJS scale as an industry standard for evaluating jailbreak risk.",
        "execSummary":  "Anthropic\u0027s publication of a structured jailbreak severity framework is a step toward standardizing how the industry measures and communicates AI safety risk ΓÇö important context for any enterprise evaluating frontier model procurement. The four-tier safety classifier taxonomy gives security and compliance teams a concrete vocabulary to assess vendor claims and design internal acceptable-use policies. For customer-support and operations leaders deploying AI that handles sensitive data, the CJS scale provides a lens for evaluating whether a model\u0027s safeguards match the threat surface of their use case. The broader implication: as frontier models become more capable, organizations need formal AI risk frameworks ΓÇö and Anthropic is shaping what that vocabulary looks like.",
